
obtain the shift value from the command line or quit

read the first character
while not end of the inpt do:
	if the char is alphabetic:
		make it lower case
		make it contain its place in the alphabet 
		add the shift value to it
		if it's fallen off the end of the alphabet, 
			shift it back in
		make it alphabetic again, instead of just it's place
	end of the if
	print the character
	read the next character
end loop: (check if we run it again)

print a line feed
quit


